{
  "texts": [
    "The key challenges addressed in building the automated tool include: 1) Data integration from multiple sources about the electrolyte performance at low temperatures; 2) Automated feature selection and extraction to highlight the low-temperature features of electrolytes; 3) Optimization of the experimental workflows to collect the battery performance under low temperature.",
    "By integrating variables across different scales in batteries, we can accelerate the research and development of new electrolytes for batteries employed at low temperature.",
    "We believe that this automation tool can be significant for the discovery of new battery materials for other predetermined conditions.",
    "Dual-drive application of theory and ML-guided investigations Though ML is powerful, its backend mechanism is like a black box, the explanation of the ML model makes it challenging for us to understand the backend theory of all the problems.",
    "In Fig. 8c, it is essential if we can draw conclusions from the black box of ML models and propose a new theory for the battery science community."
  ]
}